# PearPaste mobile Pear-end bundling — bare-pack configuration.
#
# This documents the exact invocation the mobile build uses to turn the Bare
# worklet (mobile/backend/worklet.mjs) + the shared backend/ Pear-end into a
# single linked bundle that react-native-bare-kit loads on iOS and Android.
#
# bare-pack 2.0.1 is a CLI (no JSON config file format). This file documents
# the canonical local command + rationale; Android Gradle and BUILD.md
# reference it.
#
# Spec refs: §13 (mobile packaging), §17 (release).

# ---- Entry -----------------------------------------------------------------
# The worklet entry. It imports ../backend/index.js (the SAME Pear-end as
# desktop) and serves bare-rpc. bare-pack follows the import graph from here.
ENTRY=mobile/backend/worklet.mjs

# ---- Output ----------------------------------------------------------------
# The linked bundles consumed by react-native-bare-kit. React Native imports
# `../../backend/worklet-bundle`, which Metro resolves to the per-platform shim
# and then to one of the generated CommonJS modules below.
OUT_ALL=mobile/backend/app.bundle.js
OUT_ANDROID=mobile/backend/app.android.bundle.js
OUT_IOS=mobile/backend/app.ios.bundle.js

# ---- Command (run from repo root) -----------------------------------------
# --linked  : produce a single linked bundle (required by react-native-bare-kit)
# --host    : resolve linked native addon refs for each mobile host triple
#
#   npm --prefix mobile/PearPasteMobile run bundle:bare
#
# Equivalent expanded command, using the pinned RN host devDependency:
#
#   node mobile/scripts/bundle-bare.mjs

# ---- Notes -----------------------------------------------------------------
# * Native modules: corestore/hypercore/hyperswarm/sodium-native pull Bare
#   native addons. bare-pack resolves the ios/android prebuilds; the native
#   PearPaste app must link the produced .a/.aar (see mobile/BUILD.md).
# * sodium-native@5 has no crypto_auth_hmacsha256 — the backend already handles
#   crypto portably; the mobile bundle does NOT add or patch crypto.
# * The bundle is platform-neutral JS + linked addon refs; producing the final
#   .ipa/.apk requires Xcode / Android SDK and is OUT OF SCOPE of this repo
#   (documented honestly in mobile/BUILD.md).
